The Toyota Prius (/ˈpriːəs/) is a full hybrid electric mid-size hatchback developed and manufactured by [MASK].

The Prius family totaled global cumulative sales of 5.2 million units in July 2015, representing 65.4% of the 8 million hybrids sold worldwide by [MASK] since 1997.

The Apple III (often styled as Apple ///) is a business-oriented personal computer produced and released by [MASK] that was intended as the successor to the Apple II series, but was largely considered a failure in the market.
Development stopped and the Apple III was discontinued on April 24, 1984, and its last successor—the III Plus, was dropped from the [MASK] product line in September 1985.
